This paper is about using deep learning models for malware classification, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on feature engineering, which is a key aspect of machine learning and falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of training data volume and regularization on the quality of the learned features, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and neural networks (cs.NE).
